Author: Thomas Müller <git@tom94.net>
Date:   Tue Dec 16 07:32:30 2025 +0800

    fix(colors): always mirror srgb (inv-)transfer about zero

    This change shouldn't affect correctness, because the non-mirrored sRGB
    transfer function is only defined in the interval 0 to 1. However, in
    some edge cases where images contain YUV data, and extended sRGB
    transfer function (flipped about 0) has to be used, which was previously
    handled incorrectly. This is mostly a theoretical concern, though, since
    I have never seen an image in the wild where negative values actually
    occurred.
