    feat(heic,avif,jxl,png): attempt to extract maxCLL and maxFALL

    heic, avif, and png can carry metadata about their absolute brightness
    in terms of maxCLL and maxFALL. Among my suite of test images I only
    found a single source (Eric Chan's HDR sample images) that actually
    carry this metadata -- and it's somewhat redundant because the PQ
    transfer function already serves the same role. Still useful to read,
    just in case.

    jxl contains "target_intensity" metadata, which is not quite defined the
    way maxCLL is, but Eric Chan seems to have used it analogously in his
    same images, so I am going to interpret non-default values of this field
    as maxCLL for now. Again, none of my other JXL test images (including
    libjxl's official conformance suite) actually carry this info, and in
    Eric Chan's case, the PQ transfer made it obsolete. But, just in case
    there are floating point JXLs with non-default "target_intensity" out
    there, tev'll read it.
